-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Wed Jul 23, 2014 05:58AM EDT
-- None



July 23 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 0930 GMT on Wednesday:

** Medium-sized lender Philippine Bank of Communications <PBC.PS> said on Wednesday that businessman-retailer Lucio Co would buy more than a third of the bank for nearly 6 billion pesos ($139 million), the latest in a wave of mergers and acquisitions in the local banking sector. [ID:nL4N0PY1W3]  ** Japan's Itochu Corp <8001.T> and Sumitomo Corp <8053.T> want to sell their stakes in two Australian coal mines and a coal terminal they co-own with Glencore Plc <GLEN.L>, two people familiar with the matter said on Wednesday. [ID:nL4N0PY27M]  ** State-backed British lender Royal Bank of Scotland <RBS.L> is considering selling its Irish unit Ulster Bank to a private equity firm, the Irish Examiner reported on Wednesday, citing unnamed sources. [ID:nL6N0PY1Y0]  ** Polish cable operator Vectra said on Wednesday that it had increased its bid for a 33 percent stake in telecommunication company Netia <NET.WA> to 5.41 zlotys ($1.76) per share. [ID:nW8N0PC01D]  ** Saudi Arabia's Savola Group <2050.SE> has signed a non-binding agreement to sell its packaging business to Takween Advanced Industries <1201.SE>, as it moves to focus on its core sectors of food and retailing, it said on Wednesday. [ID:nL6N0PY1AF]  ** JPMorgan Chase & Co <JPM.N> is close to a deal to sell half its private equity business, One Equity Partners, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL4N0PX64T]  ** Spanish oil company Repsol SA <REP.MC> is considering a bid for Canada-based Talisman Energy Inc <TLM.TO> <TLM.N>, Bloomberg reported, citing people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0PY0A8]  ** Canadian dairy cooperative Agropur said on Tuesday that it would acquire the dairy processing assets of Davisco Foods International Inc. [ID:nL4N0PX5Z9]